I would recommend keeping your left and right positioning at 50% with a transform of -50% on both X and Y. No more calculations or javascript necessary.

Remove your inline css added dynamically and update your css to be:

    #one {
        width: 80px;
        height: 80px;
        background-color: red;
        position: absolute;
        border-radius: 50%;
        transition: all 2s;
        left: 50%;
        top: 50%;
        transform: translate(-50%, -50%);
    }

You don&#39;t need any JS for that, you can center an Element just with CSS inside its offset-parent:
 
```CSS
position: absolute;
left: 50%; 
top: 50%; 
transform: translate(-50%, -50%);
```


